'''Educaedu''' is an online education directory where students can search for higher education programs around the world. Founded in 2001, Educaedu originally started in Spain with three Web sites (Busca Opposiciones, Tu Master and Canal Cursos). In January 2008, they decided to expand the directory and launch Educaedu on a global scale. It now operates in 20 countries and 9 different languages, and contains more than 100,000 different programs.<ref>[http://www.panoramadelpuerto.info/rev2/noticia.php?panorama=2066 "Panomara del Puerto"]</ref><ref>[http://www.cnnexpansion.com/mi-carrera/2010/01/11/tu-proxima-universidad-esta-en-internet "CNN Extension"].</ref>

Educaedu has '''105 people''' with '''15 different nationalities'''. Educaedu has offices in Buenos Aires (Argentina), Bilbao (Spain), São Paulo (Brazil), Bogotá (Colombia),  Madrid (Spain) and Mexico City (Mexico), and has a representative in Santiago (Chile).

As of December 2010, Educaedu operates in the following countries:

Argentina,<ref>[http://www.lanacion.com.ar/nota.asp?nota_id=1073131 "La Nacion"]</ref> Australia, Austria, Brazil, Canada, Chile, Colombia,<ref>"El Colombiano"</ref> Ecuador, France, Germany, Italy, Mexico,<ref>"Yahoo Mexico"</ref><ref>"Universia Mexico"</ref> Peru,<ref>"Universia Peru"</ref> Poland, Portugal, Russia, Spain, Turkey, UK, United States.

Languages: English, Spanish, French, German, Italian, Polish, Portuguese, Russian and Turkish.

