'''Philip Snow Gang''' is the founder and Academic Dean of TIES (The Institute for Educational Studies),<ref>{{cite web|title=Faculty|url=http://www.ties-edu.org/mil/faculty/|publisher=TIES|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> Montessori academic,<ref name="BoydBrewer1993">{{cite book|author1=Chris Boyd|author2=Chris Brewer|title=Freedom to Fly: 101 Activities for Building Self-Worth|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HmlRAAAAYAAJ|date=June 1993|publisher=Zephyr Press|isbn=978-0-913705-84-1}}</ref> historian and eco-cosmological educator.<ref>{{cite web|title=Philip Snow Gang|url=http://aboutplacejournal.org/primal-paradox/s5-iii-iii/philip-gang-iii-iii/|publisher=About Place Journal|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> In the mid 1980s, Gang, in collaboration with Ron Miller, helped to popularize the term "[[holistic education]]",<ref name=psg>{{cite web|title=Chapter 1|url=http://chapters.scarecrowpress.com/15/788/1578866324ch2.pdf|publisher=Scare Crow Press|accessdate=2 March 2016}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and he served as a leading advocate for the movement on the International stage. Gang also collaborated with the UN University for Peace who helped plant the seeds to create the Global Alliance for Transforming Education,<ref>{{cite web|title=Steps toward a Global Education System See Steps toward Global Mind Control|url=http://www.crossroad.to/Books/BraveNewSchools/Chronology.htm|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> and was an important figure in popularizing the [[Montessori in the United States|Montessori schooling methods for use in the United States]].<ref name=psg>{{cite web|title=Chapter 1|url=http://chapters.scarecrowpress.com/15/788/1578866324ch2.pdf|publisher=Scare Crow Press|accessdate=2 March 2016}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In the late 1980s Dr. Gang took part in the Global Thinking Project. As a Citizen Diplomat he traveled to Russia and was in dialogue with teachers, principals and directors of the Soviet Academy. Most significant was the Siberian lecture on Ecology where he presented ''Our Planet Our Home''.<ref name="HassardWeisberg1999">{{cite book|author1=Jack Hassard|author2=Julie Weisberg|title=Environmental Science on the Net: The Global Thinking Project|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eZPwiyxqEA0C&pg=PA258|year=1999|publisher=Good Year Books|isbn=978-0-673-57732-0|pages=258–}}</ref>

==Early life==
Philip Snow Gang was the son of George and Fannie Gang. George owned Anoroc Products, manufacturing glass and aluminum for shower and patio doors, which he ran with Philip's brother Daniel.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alumni Mag|url=https://issuu.com/gtalumni/docs/1962_41_1/30|publisher=Georgia Tech Alumni Mag|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> Gang attended Forest Hills High School.<ref>{{cite web|title=Forest Hills High School Class of 1958|url=http://www.e-yearbook.com/yearbooks/Forest_Hills_High_School_Forester_Yearbook/1958/Page_105.html|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>

==Montessori Schooling Methods==
In 1967, Gang first came into contact with Montessori at the Ashdun Hall Montessori,<ref name="Martin2011">{{cite book|author=Harold H. Martin|title=Atlanta and Environs: A Chronicle of Its People and Events, 1940s-1970s|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=W1pfjlqKhlMC&pg=PA438|date=1 March 2011|publisher=University of Georgia Press|isbn=978-0-8203-3906-1|pages=438–}}</ref> one of the first schools opened during the re-emergence of Montessori schools in the 60s in the United States.In 1973, Gang decided to move his family to Italy to study the Montessori Elementary Education Method at the Centro Internazionale Di Studi Montessoriani.<ref name=gangw>{{cite journal|last1=BETSY|first1=WHITE|journal=: The Atlanta Journal and The Atlanta Constitution Page|title=Engineer changes gears, becomes educational pioneer|date=November 13, 1986}}</ref> There, he was trained by the Italians Eleanor Honegger and Camillo Grazzini, who delivered most lectures in a combination of Italian and English.<ref name="gangw"/>

==Founding TIES and Forming GATE==
Gang met Robert Muller, then Assistant Secretary of the UN, in 1984.<ref name=wawas>{{cite web|title=Cosmos, Gaia and Spirit Symposium Presenter|url=http://earthties.org/cosmos-gaia-spirit-symposium-presenter/|accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref> Muller had previously released the "World Core Curriculum", and Gang noticed many similarities to Maria Montessori's cosmic education.<ref name="wawas"/> Muller collaborated with Gang to initiate the Global Alliance for Transforming Education, which was released in 1990. This initiative was set into motion with the 1990 publication of "The Chicago Statement on Education".<ref>Miller, Ron. 1992. "Introducing Holistic Education: The Historical and Pedagogical Context of the 1990 Chicago Statement". Teacher Education Quarterly 19 (1). Caddo Gap Press: 5–13. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23475623.</ref>
In 1990, Gang is named Executive Director of the newly formed GATE (Global Alliance for Transforming Education), an initiative started with Ron Miller and Edward Clark,<ref name="Schiller2014">{{cite book|author=Susan A. Schiller|title=Sustaining the Writing Spirit: Holistic Tools for School and Home|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D63zAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA10|date=25 February 2014|publisher=R&L Education|isbn=978-1-61048-958-4|pages=10–}}</ref> and strongly influenced Miller. GATE also released "Education 2000: A Holistic Perspective"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Miller|first1=Jack|title=HOLISTIC EDUCATION:  LEARNING FOR AN  INTERCONNECTED WORLD|url=http://www.eolss.net/sample-chapters/c11/e6-61-04-01.pdf|accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref> in 1991, which offered ten principles of holistic education.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rudge|first1=L|title=Holistic education: An analysis of its pedagogical application. Ph.D. Dissertation, The Ohio State University, Columbus, Oh, U.S.A.|url=https://www.academia.edu/1293004/Rudge_L._2008_._Holistic_education_An_analysis_of_its_pedagogical_application._Ph.D._Dissertation_The_Ohio_State_University_Columbus_Oh_U.S.A|accessdate=3 March 2016|date=2008}}</ref> He presented these concepts to audiences throughout Europe, Asia, North and South America, and Oceania.

==Books==
* Rethinking Education -  PS Gang {{ISBN|0-9623783-0-5}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gang|first1=Philip|title=Rethinking Education|url=http://www.ties-edu.org/documents/Rethinking.pdf|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref>
* Conscious Education - PS Gang {{ISBN|0-9623783-2-1}} <ref>{{cite web|last1=Gang|first1=Philip S.|last2=; And Others|title=Conscious Education: The Bridge to Freedom|url=http://eric.ed.gov/?id=ED361845|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref>

